All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Bicycle
Represents a bicycle in the vehicle rental system.
Car
Represents a car in the vehicle system.
CityMap
The CityMap class represents a grid-based map used to manage vehicle movements and their visualization.
DailyReport
The DailyReport class represents a summary of financial and operational metrics for a particular day.
DailyReportsGenerator
The DailyReportsGenerator class is responsible for generating daily financial reports based on the receipts.
DeserializationController
This controller class handles the deserialized vehicles table view in the GUI.
ICharging
This interface defines the contract for charging battery-powered vehicles.
Location
Represents a location in a 2D coordinate system.
MainApplication
The MainApplication class is the main entry point of the application.
Malfunction
Represents a malfunction that occurs in a vehicle.
MalfunctionsTableController
This controller class handles the malfunctions table view in the GUI.
MalfunctionWrapper
This class serves as a wrapper for malfunction data to be displayed in a GUI table.
MapController
The MapController class is responsible for managing the graphical representation of a map in the application using a GridPane.
Receipt
The Receipt class generates and stores financial information for a specific vehicle rental.
Rental
This class represents a rental transaction for a vehicle, tracking details such as the rental date, user information, vehicle ID, and the movement of the vehicle from start to end location on a simulated map.
RentalLoader
The RentalLoader class is responsible for loading rental data from a CSV file and populating the application's list of rentals.
ReportsController
The ReportsController class is responsible for controlling the GUI of the reports screen.
Scooter
Represents a scooter in the vehicle system.
SummaryReport
The SummaryReport class is responsible for generating and printing a summary report of the rental receipts.
Vehicle
Represents an abstract base class for all vehicles in the system.
VehicleController
This controller class handles the display of vehicles (cars, bicycles, scooters) in separate tables within the GUI.
VehicleLoader
The VehicleLoader class is responsible for loading vehicle data from a CSV file and adding the vehicles to the application's main vehicle list.
VehicleSerializer
This class handles the serialization and deserialization of Vehicle objects.
VehicleUtils
The VehicleUtils class provides utility methods for working with vehicles.
